.One case was returning from Saudi arabia .

12 the above samples were taken from sudanese returning from Hajj 2 of which are positive for H1N1 .
A localized spread was observed in higher secndary school students after  returning from a holiday break .

Preliminary data on influenza clinical reports started late February, and from 1st of March specimens were submitted from cases in Nabeul, Sfax, Sidi Bouzid and Tunis. Influenza A(H3N2) virus isolations were from cases in Sidi Bouzid, and 6 additional cases showed seroconversion to this influenza type.
Fourth week of regional activity, most cases identified to date were influenza A, subtype A(H3N2).
first cases of influenza detected for the season, 2  cases identified by direct IF and 3 cases diagnosed by serological tests, all cases were in Tunis; the 3 are A/Panama/2007-like strains

A/H3 activity moved from south (Zarzis) to southeast (Isle of Djerba)
A/H1 activity started in Tunis governorate (1 positive on 4 samples)

Flu is almost well implemented in all regions. A/H1 is still circulating well in Tunis (1 isolate) and A/H3 in south had been confermed by seroconversion against A/H3/Wyoming reference antigens in pairs of sera (1/20 to 1/512)
One B case isolate confirmed by serology in Gabs and another one (by serology) in pediatric unit in Tunis.
still A/H1 in south , 2 in Medenine and one in Ben Gardane.
beginning of the slowering of the outbreaks

from may 15th we stop systematic surveillance since activity is sporadic from 3 weeks ago and influenza season is passed. We keep an emergency avian flu testing if one or small human /animal case-related is signaled. If so, it will be promptly reporetd to WHO
slowering of the sampling in the north of the country, only 3 south governorates still adress samples
one A/H3 strain isolated in South (Sfax). Circulaion continue to be sporadic
Local outbreak of influenza B in Medenine continue
another A/H3 case in Gabes. Seasonal Flu seems to be a mix between A/H3 and B at regional level, we are waiting samples from other regions to see more clearly what other circulating flu strains do
A/H1 dominates in the North. Still a mix between A/H3 and B in the south
slowering in detecting cases in 4 governorates
Second sporadic case in Tunis in two weeks

one A/H3 virus detected in Gabes.
it seems that flu viruses are beginning to circulate locally without sread to adjacent governorates
stll gabes in regional outbreak with A Flu activity signaled clinically in Sfax (governorate close to gabes)
a second wave of A/H1 influenza cases isolated only in gabes (south) but whole country in under ILI , with A/H3 isolated in most of the governorates from january 2009
only 3 governorates still sending samples this week (Sfax, Gabes and Nabeul)

One A/H1N1 v from one Canadian citizen working in an international bank at Tunis and coming from ottawa 26 symptomatic on 28 june detected positive 30 june Second case from a baby 10 month old coming also from Ottawa the 28 june symptomatic on

10 imported and 3 secondary cases detected this week , we are slowly but surely going into the introduction of the pandemic virus in the population and we expect beginning of an outbreak when the weather condition downheat and the schools re-op
no confirmed cas of new pandemic virus this week , and seasonal flu survey is also nil.

still first index cases related in the french college continuing his outbreak (15 cases). One secondaryoutbreak close related cases in a primary school nearby (3 cases). 2 cases from another primary college with no relation ship with the index

local outbreak from the french college is at an end , first 2 cases of seasonal Flu A/H3 detected in two governorates , Bizerte at notrh and Le Kef in Central West of the country. So we downed the situation in sporadic cases this week

AH1N1 v epidemia has started in relative local outbreaks in7 from 24 governorates which send positive samples . All ceses age age 4-30 in 90% and from scholar origin with secondary cases (23 on 50 ) in close contact transmission. More than 80%
all regions are in community and scholar epidemic.
epidemic is still at a peak. One fatal case this week also

3 weeks without any pandemic case A/H1N1.
first A/H3 seasonal case in a 5 old year child (region of gabes in the south)

First Influenza B case in the south at matmata
still RSV virus predominant in children's hospital

2 A/H3 in Mareth(South) where local outbreak started 2 weeks ago. 2 A/H1N1 pdm found one in nabeul, the other one in Tunis from 2 lybians coming from lybia
1 B strain isolated at Boussalem near the frontier of Algeria

Co circulation of Flu B and A/H1N1 pdm in the governorate of Monastir this week, active circulation of A/H1N1 pdm in 5 other governorates(Tunis.Sousse, Kairouan, Gabes and Sfax)
starting of bronchiolitis season at children's hospital, Tunis

6 different governorates this week sended samples positive to A/H3
2 fatal cases due to Influenza B this week

one case of A/H1N1 pdm returning from Djeddah in KSA

one positive A/H1 pdm from a tunisian pilgrim turning back from KSA

Flu A/H1 is an 93 old women SARI case turning back from KSA after Omra !
Last report , NIC stays in stand-by until first week of October 2017

WCR_COMMENT: The measles samples were processed by another department for measles surviellance but intially reported as influenza .
Cases started to flow to the centre from hospitals and private clinics .Some of them were purely endogenous majority are children and teenagers .
2 deaths were associated with the untypable FluA samples and H1N12009 pandemic this week .
influenza cases diagnosed by serology.
third week of regional activity
Same situation as last week with A/H1 still in the south and Tunis and A/H3 growing circulation
there is still a pocket of A/H1 circulating in the gulf of Gabes , other regions with exception of Tunis do not send samples

Xe receive on 1st November the WHO influenza reagent kit and from 2 november started the epidemiologic survey in Tunisia. One case of Influenza B in Gabes , respiratory virus activity in Tunisia is still sporadic
Sporadic activity with A/H1 dominating still continued in South(Gabes and Sfax). a first A/H3 was detected in Gabes. Serologic confirmation for the previous A/H1 cases was obtained

A/H1 still growing in the south but central and west regions coming to send samples positive for A/H1. Note that 3 A/H3 positive were found in Monastir region in centre -east . So we can upgrade to local outbreaks in Tunisia.
all governorates  have signaled influenza cases. A/H1 still the most isolated but in Monastir and Tunis sporadic cases of A/H3 have begun
still a mix between A/H1 and A/H3, H1 predominating in the south and H3 in the north (Tunis and Bizerte)

A/H3 predominate now in 3 governorates Tunis, Sfax and Medenine.
Also there is a lot of influenza symptoms in vaccinated people , so we started a serologic study in vaccinated people that are not probably well protected against A/H3 to verify.
first case of Flu  A /H3 detected in a 14 year student in the South (governorate of Sfax)
Local outbreak of influenza B in Medenine (south)
outbreak in a military oasis with 120 cases of influenza B type. Still many clinical cases reported from all governorates
Sporadic case of A/H1 discovered in Tunis
start of regional outbreak in gabes where 2 A/H3 and one A/H1 strain isolated
One A/H1N1 2009 pandemic detected on an Tunis Air  Hostess returning from Kingdom of Saudi Arabia

still some cases collected with the first outbreak in Tunis. All regions are sending samples with no influenza activity and without any A/H1N1 dtection. So we wait more cold temperature conditions to see sreading of the pandemic virus.

almost 5 governorates are in regional outbreak(Tunis, Ariana, Bizerte, Nabeul and Sfax) we deplored also the first 2 fatal cases (one in Mahdia and one in Tunis) which died from fulminant influenza after 3 days illness.
To date, 17 fatal cases confirmed by PCR including 3 pregnant women
reapparition of RSV bronchiolitis in children samples signs the end of the epidemia in Tunis
same situation as last week , the period is dominated by pther respiratory viruses.
A/H1N1 pdm isolated in 5 different governorates , still Flu B circulation

Confirmation of the starting season of RSV bronchiolitis in children hospital Tunis with one fatal case in a baby of 3 months
Also first fatal case by A/H3 virus in a 16 years old student in Tunis
We send last week to NIMR London, the first 2 A/H3 strains found in Tunisia for sequencing
Influenza A/H3 found in a fatal case in Tunis, Influenza A/H1 pdm in a young in Sfax
2 A/H3 isolated in Tunis from one patient coming from germany which passed the virus to his mother
all positive strains for flu (4) are imported from KSA with pilgrims returning from Omra (still no Mers-CoV cases detected in 2014)
the 3 flu cases are turning back from Hadjj (KSA) and are negative for MERS-CoV
